title: Top 20 Landholders in Fresno County pre-1892
name: Top 20 Landholders in Fresno County pre-1892
description:
This file contains all patents filed by the twenty largest landholders in Fresno County at the end of 1891, as measured in number of patents filed. At the time that Thomas Thompson's county atlas was produced, many of them had sold their land. However, their presence had profoundly impacted settlement patterns in Fresno County, and there was a negative correlation between the land that they had initially held and so called markers of development, like schools and post offices.
For further analyses and commentary, please read Cameron Ormsby's article "Land Speculation in Fresno County: 1860-1891" at the following address: http://www.stanford.edu/group/spatialhistory/cgi-bin/site/pub.php?id=67
Sources: Fresno County Atlas (1891) created by Thomas H. Thompson, Land Patent Database from State of California
